{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|いわお}}

{{IPAchar|/ipa po/}} → {{IPAchar|/ifafo/}} → {{IPAchar|/iwawo/}} → {{IPAchar|/iwao/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=いわお|-}}.  Found in the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'' finished some time after 759 CE.<ref>{{RQ:Manyoshu|19|4231}}, text [http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man19Yo.html#4231 here]</ref>

Originally a compound of {{compound|ja|sort=いわお|岩|tr1=ipa → iwa|t1=boulder; crag|秀|tr2=po → ho|t2=something tall and prominent|pos2=cognate with {{m|ja|穂||tr=ho|ear of grain}}, from the sense of ''something prominent sticking upwards''}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="SMK5">{{R:Shinmeikai5}}</ref>

The character is Japanese [[shinjitai]], simplified from {{ja-l|巖}}.

